keywords: ["Type 2 Diabetes", "GLP-1", "Small Molecule", "Glucose Homeostasis", "Clinical Trials"]
abstract: |
  Current treatments for Type 2 Diabetes often involve frequent injections 
  or have significant side effects. We report the development and early-phase 
  testing of WP-450, a potent oral small molecule inhibitor of dipeptidyl 
  peptidase-4 (DPP-4). In a multi-center randomized controlled trial, 
  WP-450 significantly reduced HbA1c levels compared to placebo over 12 weeks.
